<p>Subsec. (k)(2)(B) to (D). <a href="/rio/citation/Pub._L._109-58">Pub. L. 109–58, § 1504(a)(1)(A)(ii)</a>, (iii), redesignated subpars. (C) and (D) as (B) and (C), respectively, and struck out heading and text of former subpar. (B). Text read as follows: “The oxygen content of the gasoline shall equal or exceed 2.0 percent by weight (subject to a testing tolerance established by the<a aria-label="Definitions -  Administrator)" class="colorbox-load definedterm" href="/definitions/uscode.php?width=840&amp;height=800&amp;iframe=true&amp;def_id=42-USC-146731693-1186899454&amp;term_occur=999&amp;term_src="> Administrator)</a> except as otherwise required by this chapter. The<a aria-label="Definitions -  Administrator " class="colorbox-load definedterm" href="/definitions/uscode.php?width=840&amp;height=800&amp;iframe=true&amp;def_id=42-USC-146731693-1186899454&amp;term_occur=999&amp;term_src="> Administrator </a>may waive, in whole or in part, the application of this subparagraph for any ozone nonattainment area upon a determination by the<a aria-label="Definitions -  Administrator " class="colorbox-load definedterm" href="/definitions/uscode.php?width=840&amp;height=800&amp;iframe=true&amp;def_id=42-USC-146731693-1186899454&amp;term_occur=999&amp;term_src="> Administrator </a>that compliance with such requirement would prevent or interfere with the attainment by the area of a national primary ambient air quality standard.”</p>
