 district in which he does business. The<a aria-label="Definitions -  Administrator " class="colorbox-load definedterm" href="/definitions/uscode.php?width=840&amp;height=800&amp;iframe=true&amp;def_id=42-USC-146731693-1186899454&amp;term_occur=999&amp;term_src="> Administrator </a>may, upon application therefor, remit or mitigate any forfeiture provided for in this subsection and he shall have authority to determine the facts upon all such applications.”</p>
